obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_1254  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In this report, Geerts et al study the dynamic distribution of tomosyn-1 in mouse hippocampal neurons. By applying immunoelectron microscopy, immunocytochemistry and live imaging, the authors show localization of tomosyn-1 to dense core vesicles in EM images and indirectly by co-labelling with the DCV marker chromogranin B (Fig 2, 4). Furthermore, time-lapse images and coresponding kymographs supports these findings by showing co-migration tomosyn with neuropeptide Y, a DCV marker (Fig. 5).. Experimental description: Neuronal cultures\nAnimals were housed, bred and experimentally used according to Institutional guidelines and\nDutch and U.S. governmental laws with prior approval from the institutional animal research\nethics committee (\"Dierexperimentencommissie Vrije Universiteit/VU medisch centrum\";\napproval number FGA11-03), ensuring minimum discomfort of animals. All procedures were\napproved by the C57BL/6 wild type mice were obtained from Harlan (Horst, The Netherlands).\nTom-1KO/KO and Syt-1KO/KO mice were described [22,34]. E18 stage embryos were\nobtained by Caesarean section of pregnant females from timed matings. H\n\n5/2/2018 Pim\n- Overexpressed Tomosyn-1 (syntaxin-binding protein 5) is of mouse species: \"An EYFP-tag was fused to the N-terminus of mouse tomosyn-m1 (Genbank accession number NP_001074813.2) ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1254" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

<http://identifiers.org/mgi/MGI:1926058>
